.TH "devm_kstrdup_const" 9 "devm_kstrdup_const" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_kstrdup_const \- resource managed conditional string duplication
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const char *" devm_kstrdup_const
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const char *s "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device for which to duplicate the string
.IP "s" 12
the string to duplicate
.IP "gfp" 12
the GFP mask used in the \fBkmalloc\fP call when allocating memory
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Strings allocated by devm_kstrdup_const will be automatically freed when
the associated device is detached.
.SH "RETURN"
Source string if it is in .rodata section otherwise it falls back to
devm_kstrdup.
